   <div xml:lang="en" style="1">
    <p begin="00:00:01.31" dur="00:00:02.03">&gt;&gt; Joyce: Hi, this is Joyce<br/>Farrell.</p>
    <p begin="00:00:03.34" dur="00:00:02.85">Here's a quick introduction<br/>to loops.</p>
    <p begin="00:00:06.19" dur="00:00:03.52">A loop structure executes<br/>continuously while some</p>
    <p begin="00:00:09.71" dur="00:00:02.30">condition remains true.</p>
    <p begin="00:00:12.01" dur="00:00:02.90">For example, suppose<br/>you ask a question,</p>
    <p begin="00:00:14.91" dur="00:00:01.76">"Are you still mad at me?"</p>
    <p begin="00:00:16.67" dur="00:00:02.44">The result is a Boolean<br/>answer,</p>
    <p begin="00:00:19.11" dur="00:00:02.65">yes or no, true or false.</p>
    <p begin="00:00:21.76" dur="00:00:02.62">Suppose the answer is yes.</p>
    <p begin="00:00:24.38" dur="00:00:05.35">Something must change and then<br/>the question can be asked again,</p>
    <p begin="00:00:29.73" dur="00:00:02.37">"Are you still made at me?"</p>
    <p begin="00:00:32.10" dur="00:00:02.21">Suppose the answer is yes.</p>
    <p begin="00:00:34.31" dur="00:00:04.07">Then something must change and<br/>you can ask the question again.</p>
    <p begin="00:00:38.38" dur="00:00:03.71">While the answer remains<br/>yes, something must change</p>
    <p begin="00:00:42.09" dur="00:00:02.65">and you can ask the<br/>question again.</p>
    <p begin="00:00:44.74" dur="00:00:03.13">When the answer is<br/>no, the loop ends.</p>
    <p begin="00:00:47.87" dur="00:00:04.18">The loop continues while<br/>the condition was true.</p>
    <p begin="00:00:52.05" dur="00:00:00.92">Thanks for watching.</p>
   </div>
